      "description": "Massless two-loop sunrise family with external momentum $k$, $k^2=s$. Three propagators $D_1=l_1^2$, $D_2=l_2^2$, $D_3=(l_1+l_2+k)^2$ plus two ISPs $D_4=l_1 \\cdot k$, $D_5=l_2 \\cdot k$. All sub-sector integrals are scaleless and vanish. The top sector contains only 3 master integrals. Explicit DEs $A_4, A_5$ of the GFs w.r.t. $x_4,x_5$ and an explicit closed-form recurrence relation (Eq. 29) reducing $I(\\nu_4,\\nu_5)$ to $I(0,0)$ are given, as well as $\\eta$-type DEs (4 MIs) for arbitrary powers of denominators. Used to illustrate that the fixed-direction scheme gives DEs already in canonical form.",
